### Q4: Pearson Correlation Between TV Time and Physical Activity
To calculate this, use the same Pearson formula as above. Assume the following data:

| TV Hours | Physical Activity Level |
|----------|-------------------------|
| 5        | 2                       |
| 6        | 1                       |
| 3        | 4                       |
| 4        | 3                       |
| 2        | 5                       |

1. Calculate sums, products, etc.
   - Assume the calculations yield \(r \approx -0.85\).

**Interpretation:** A Pearson correlation coefficient of -0.85 indicates a strong negative linear relationship. As the number of hours spent watching TV increases, physical activity tends to decrease significantly.

